@startuml network_architecture_driving_alert_active_baseline
!theme plain
top to bottom direction
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #4D4D4D
skinparam PackageBorderColor #808080
skinparam ComponentBorderColor #808080
skinparam NoteBorderColor #808080
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FAFAFA

title Level 2: Integrated Warning Network Topology\n(Domain CAN + ETH Backbone + Gateway Boundary)

rectangle "Context Owner Domain" as DOMAIN_CONTEXT #F7F7F7 {
  component "VCU" as VCU #FFFFFF
  component "MDPS" as MDPS #FFFFFF
  component "NAV / IVI" as IVI #FFFFFF
}

rectangle "Decision / Boundary Domain" as DOMAIN_CORE #F2F2F2 {
  component "V2X\nEmergency Context Owner" as V2X #FFFFFF
  component "ADAS\nWarning / Risk Decision Owner" as ADAS #FFFFFF
  component "CGW\nBoundary / Fail-Safe Authority" as CGW #FFFFFF
}

rectangle "Render / Output Domain" as DOMAIN_RENDER #F7F7F7 {
  component "BCM" as BCM #FFFFFF
  component "CLU" as CLU #FFFFFF
  component "HUD" as HUD #FFFFFF
  component "AMP" as AMP #FFFFFF
}

rectangle "Validation / Diagnostic Domain" as DOMAIN_VALID #F7F7F7 {
  component "TEST_SCN\nValidation Stimulus" as TESTSCN #FFFFFF
  component "TEST_BAS\nBaseline Observer" as TESTBAS #FFFFFF
  component "SGW / DCM / EXT_DIAG" as DIAG #FFFFFF
}

queue "Chassis CAN\n0x100 ~ 0x13F" as CAN_CHASSIS #FFFFFF
queue "Infotainment CAN\n0x280 ~ 0x29F" as CAN_INFO #FFFFFF
queue "Body CAN\n0x260 ~ 0x27F" as CAN_BODY #FFFFFF
cloud "ETH Backbone\nUDP Multicast 239.0.2.1:5000" as ETHB #FFFFFF

VCU -- CAN_CHASSIS
MDPS -- CAN_CHASSIS
IVI -- CAN_INFO
BCM -- CAN_BODY
CLU -- CAN_INFO
HUD -- CAN_INFO
AMP -- CAN_INFO

CAN_CHASSIS --> CGW : vehicle / steering context
CAN_INFO --> CGW : route / zone / speed-limit context

V2X -- ETHB
ADAS -- ETHB
CGW -- ETHB
TESTSCN -- ETHB
TESTBAS -- ETHB

ETHB --> V2X : ETH_EmergencyAlert (0xE100)
V2X --> ADAS : CoreState::emergencyIngress*
ADAS --> CGW : selectedAlertDecision*\ndecelAssistDecisionReq
CGW --> DOMAIN_RENDER : selectedAlertEffective*\nwarningPathStatus
ETHB ..> TESTBAS : monitor / result observation
DIAG ..> CGW : boundary observation
DIAG ..> ADAS : decision observation
DIAG ..> V2X : ingress observation

note top of ETHB
  **Backbone Contract**
  • Active transport: UDP multicast
  • Runtime identifiers:
    - 0x510 ~ 0x512 context ingress
    - 0xE100 emergency ingress
    - 0x1C2 emergency monitor
    - 0xE200 decision result
    - 0xE210 ~ 0xE216 risk / fail-safe
end note

note left of DOMAIN_CONTEXT
  **Context Publication**
  • Chassis CAN
    - frmVehicleStateCanMsg (0x2A0)
    - frmSteeringStateCanMsg (0x100)
  • Infotainment CAN
    - frmNavigationRouteMsg (0x285)
  • UDP context
    - 0x510 / 0x511 / 0x512
end note

note right of CGW
  **Boundary Rule B01**
  • warningPathStatus
  • e2eHealthState
  • failSafeMode
  • selectedAlertEffective*
  • decelAssistReq effective gate
end note

note right of DOMAIN_RENDER
  **Render Consumption**
  • BCM: ambient / hazard output
  • CLU: cluster warning
  • HUD: front display warning
  • AMP: audio guidance / ducking
end note

note bottom of TESTSCN
  **Validation Rule V01**
  • may inject emergency or object stimulus
  • may not become product owner
  • final meaning remains in V2X / ADAS / CGW
end note

legend right
  1. Domain CAN = local ECU context
  2. ETH Backbone = cross-domain warning meaning
  3. V2X = emergency normalization owner
  4. ADAS = warning / risk decision owner
  5. CGW = timeout clear / fail-safe boundary authority
  6. Render + validation + diagnostic stay separated
endlegend

@enduml
